{
  "texts": [
    "The M-JDA + NCA method is extremely helpful in identifying the location of damage in a target structure (that does not contain any damage labels), which can then be used to optimize any following repair and maintenance procedures.",
    "By using a population-based approach, it may be possible to avoid installing a network of strategically-placed sensors for damage localisation, that are essential to traditional SHM methods.",
    "Realistic applications of transfer learning are likely to encounter class imbalance where the source and target structures contain different number of classes.",
    "Consequently, this article also tested the suitability of the NCA + M-JDA method when there exists a class imbalance within the source and target domains.",
    "Classification performances remained high in some instances and reduced significantly in others."
  ]
}